>>65135479
There is a limited number of simple geometric forms available, really. It is not much of an exaggeration to say that some Neolithic culture somewhere used any given mandala to mean anything whatsoever. When I use s search engine to look for symbolism relating to spiral shapes, I get back an awful lot of stuff that has a distinct 1980s "New Age" bullshit smell about it. It's maybe a bit much to ask archaeologists to be definitive about what such and such symbol meant that such-and-such group of cavemen, who hadn't invented writing yet, whose spoken language is unknown to us, scratched into cave walls twenty thousand years ago, so, of course, 99% of what I'm finding is "this symbolizes the interconnectedness of all life and the fragility of Mother Earth, while warning against the excesses of late stage capitalism, blah blah blah." Putting the opinions of some sanctimonious Boomer pothead circa 1982 into the mouths of people who wore animal skins and lived in caves is fun and all, and sold an awful lot of books to an awful lot of future wine aunts back during the Reagan Administration, but it doesn't actually tell us anything.

>>65135578
